
[1]rational

   RA'TIONAL, a. [L. rationalis.]

   1. Having reason or the faculty of reasoning; endowed with reason;
   opposed to irrational; as, man is a rational being; brutes are not
   rational animals.

   It is our glory and happiness to have a rational nature.

   2. Agreeable to reason; opposed to absurd; as a rational conclusion or
   inference; rational conduct.

   3. Agreeable to reason; not extravagant.

   4. Acting in conformity to reason; wise; judicious; as a rational man.

                       RA'TIONAL, n. A rational being.
